4. Data Visualization & EDA

In[150]:
float_cols = [col for col in train.columns if train[col].dtype == "float64"]

cols_per_row = 3
num_plots = len(float_cols)
rows = (num_plots // cols_per_row) + (num_plots % cols_per_row > 0) 

fig, axes = plt.subplots(rows, cols_per_row, figsize=(15, 5 * rows)) 
axes = axes.flatten()  

for idx, col in enumerate(float_cols):
    sns.histplot(train[col], bins=50, kde=True, ax=axes[idx])
    axes[idx].set_title(f"Distribution of {col}")

for i in range(idx + 1, len(axes)):
    fig.delaxes(axes[i])

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

5. Feature Engineering

In[153]:
train['Weight Capacity (kg)'] = train['Weight Capacity (kg)'].fillna(train['Weight Capacity (kg)'].mean())
test['Weight Capacity (kg)'] = test['Weight Capacity (kg)'].fillna(test['Weight Capacity (kg)'].mean())
In[154]:
test['Brand'] = test['Brand'].fillna("None")
test['Material'] = test['Material'].fillna("None")
test['Size'] = test['Size'].fillna(test['Size'].mode())
test['Laptop Compartment'] = test['Laptop Compartment'].fillna(test['Laptop Compartment'].mode())
test['Waterproof'] = test['Waterproof'].fillna(test['Waterproof'].mode())
test['Style'] = test['Style'].fillna(test['Style'].mode())
test['Color'] = test['Color'].fillna(test['Color'].mode())
In[155]:
x = train.columns.intersection(test.columns)
print(x)

In[156]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

le_dict = {}  

categorical_labels = ['Brand', 'Material', 'Size', 'Laptop Compartment', 'Waterproof', 'Style', 'Color']

for col in categorical_labels:
    le = LabelEncoder()  
    train[col] = le.fit_transform(train[col])  
    test[col] = test[col].map(lambda x: le.transform([x])[0] if x in le.classes_ else -1)
    le_dict[col] = le

X = train.drop(columns=['id', 'Price'])
X_test = test.drop(columns=['id'])

y = train['Price']

model = CatBoostRegressor(cat_features=categorical_labels, task_type='GPU', devices='0')
